{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "README Index on Delete",
  "description": "Khi có file bị xóa trong .kiro/skills, .kiro/steering, .kiro/hooks, hoặc .kiro/powers — tự động cập nhật README.md, install.sh profiles, và commit + push (cần confirm).",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileDeleted",
    "patterns": [
      ".kiro/skills/**/*",
      ".kiro/steering/**/*",
      ".kiro/hooks/**/*",
      ".kiro/powers/**/*"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A Kiro component file was deleted. Please:\n1. Scan all current skills (.kiro/skills/*/SKILL.md), steering (.kiro/steering/*.md), hooks (.kiro/hooks/*.kiro.hook), and powers (.kiro/powers/*/POWER.md).\n2. Regenerate the README.md tables to reflect the current state:\n   - Skills table (count + rows) — remove deleted skill\n   - Steering table\n   - Hooks table (dev-only note)\n   - Powers table\n   - Badge counts\n   - **Installation Profiles section**: remove deleted skill from the profile table\n3. Update install.sh:\n   - Remove deleted skill from its profile function (profile_llm, profile_inference, etc.) and all_skills()\n   - If deleted steering: remove from resolve_steering() mapping\n4. Update docs/skill-interconnection-map.md — remove from layer, dependency matrix, workflow chains.\n5. After updating, run: git add . && git commit -m \"docs: update README index\" — then ask user for confirmation before git push origin main."
  }
}